  <steps>
    <step num="0">Beat the eggs into the buttermilk. </step>
    <step num="1">Add the chicken pieces to the buttermilk mixture and chill for an hour. </step>
    <step num="2">In a large mixing bowl, mix the flour with all the herbs and spices. </step>
    <step num="3">Coat the soaked chicken pieces in the herbed flour mixture, shaking off any excess. </step>
    <step num="4">Heat oil in a large sauce pan to 325˚F (170°C), then turn to low heat. </step>
    <step num="5">Fry the chicken in batches for 15 minutes until the chicken is cooked and the skins turn golden brown. </step>
    <step num="6">Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate. </step>
    <step num="7">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
